         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">The Treasury ¶ Melbourne 15th October 1894 ¶ Copy ¶ No 7768 ¶  ¶ Sir,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">94.10.16c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Charles Topp</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No.3905, pp. 10-11, unit 105, VPRS 1187/P, outward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Eaton's letter was sent on 15 October to Topp as Undersecretary, Chief Secretary's Department, and copies were forwarded by him to heads of xub-departments the next day.</p>
               </note>The Treasury</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne 15th October 1894</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Copy</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">No 7768<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am directed to inform you that the officers to whom Advances have been made for the payment of Salaries and Wages, may after the passing of the next Supply Bill<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The next Supply bill, for funds to pay for expenses incurred in 1893-94 financial year ending 30 June 1894, was passed 31 October 1894. There was no provision in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Chief Secretary's budget<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for expenditure in the Government Botanist's department<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Votes and Proceedings of the Legislative Assembly</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Session 1894-5, vol. 1, pp. 15-17).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>receive an advance to pay the difference between the amount payable under existing law, and the amount which has been paid during the past three months.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This Advance is to be adjusted as soon as practicable.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A further Advance, based on the requirements for one month only will also be made.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This Advance is to be considered as an addition to the ordinary annual salary Advance, with which it is to be adjusted at the end of the financial year.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>H. F. Eaton</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Under Treasurer</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Under Secretary</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Forwarded for the information and guidance of the [...]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Space left empty for title of the sub-department head to be entered.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Charles Topp</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">16th October 1894</p>
         </div>
